<br>
Since Mod Rods are primarily used on raids and not so often in groups, this becomes a raid specific spell.<br>
<br>
As with other group spells, you get the biggest effect from 4+ members in the group. And with Cadeau being our final Single Target DS, there's even more reason to use MGB while in raid encounters.<br>
<br>
If MMT was to become a group only spell, we're looking at a manna cost of roughly 1,600, under half the current manna cost and it makes it castable by even the un-uberest of players Level 56+! &lt;GASP&gt;<br>
<br>
Now, those Mages out there who DO have 3.3K+ manna will oppose my suggestion, but I'm not one of you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'd love to see MMT made a group spell, similar to Aegis of Ro and Boon of Immolation, at a drastic manna cut. Since MGB uses double the manna when used, cutting the manna cost in half is the sensible thing to do if you're going to remove the MGB component.<br>
<br>
Now, all the Mages are gonna scream &quot;But what about us raid Mages who want to use this spell? We're gonna have to waste even more manna!&quot;<br>
<br>
Maybe so, but the likelyhood on a raid is that there will be more than one Mage, so the burden is split and there's always Mass Group Buff &lt;if it were altered to allow MMT to be used too&gt; to do the first major distribution at the beginnign of the raid and those of us who dont have +100 manna on every slot will still be able to cast this spell, even when not on raids and without the AA skill.<br>
<br>
As I'm sure a lot of people will say &quot;When you're Lvl 65, you'll be uber enough after a zillion AA points to regret your suggestion if MGB changes&quot;. Well, I'm lvl 55, still in roughly 2.5K manna area, only 205 int and my guild ios not the uberest there is, our most challenging raid is in Kael <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I won't be heading off to Vex Thal any time soon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Nor will I be breaking the 3.5K manna pool sometime soon!<br>
<br>
My suggestion would only have an effect on the raid Mage, and even then there are plenty of ways to work around the &quot;problem&quot;, not to mention increased incentive to bring more Mages along. <p>Majishia Vie &lt;Wyrd Angles&gt;<br>
